<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-22T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-22T05:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4997: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Prince</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-22T11:00:00+01:00">August 22, 1931—11 a.m.</date><lb/>[Received August
                                        22—10:50 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                                <p>39. [Paraphrase]. Yesterday in private audience King Alexander
                                    personally requested me to send the following message to
                                    President Hoover regarding the moratorium proposal: [End
                                    paraphrase]. <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“I ask President Hoover and his advisers to consider the
                                            lamentable situation in which Yugoslavia would be placed
                                            in view of her existing financial obligations if our
                                            country should lose 888,000,000 dinars during the coming
                                            year according to the terms of the moratorium. I
                                            therefore earnestly request President Hoover to do his
                                            utmost to help us in our present dilemma of which I can
                                            see no other solution.”</p>
                                    </quote></p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Prince</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>